# main.py serves as the primary file that initiates and orchestrates the entire application. It acts as the entry point where the execution of the program begins. Within main.py, various modules and functions are called to carry out specific tasks and functionalities of the application. It serves as the central hub where different components of the application are integrated and coordinated to ensure smooth operation. Additionally, main.py may also handle user inputs, manage data flow, and control the overall flow of the program. It plays a crucial role in the overall structure and functionality of the application.